    <h1>Paris</h1>
    <p>Paris, the capital city of France, is one of the most famous and romantic cities in the world. Known as the “City of Light” (La Ville Lumière), Paris is celebrated for its rich history, breathtaking architecture, and vibrant culture. It is home to iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, Louvre Museum, Notre-Dame Cathedral, and the Champs-Élysées.</p>
    <p>SBeyond its monuments, Paris is also a global center for art, fashion, gastronomy, and philosophy. The city’s charming cafés, scenic riverbanks along the Seine River, and elegant neighborhoods make it a top destination for tourists from around the world. Whether you’re exploring art galleries, enjoying French cuisine, or simply strolling through its beautiful streets, Paris offers an unforgettable experience that combines history, beauty, and romance.</p>

